        {
            "name": "Bugbear",
            "type": "section",
            "sections": [
                {
                    "name": "Bugbear Lairs",
                    "type": "sidebar",
                    "sections": [],
                    "text": "Bugbears live in small gangs that\noften prowl together, working as a\ngroup to sow torment. They keep\ntheir lairs in hard-to-find places\ndeep in the forest or hills.",
                    "source": {
                        "name": "Bestiary",
                        "link": {
                            "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01y0m?Pathfinder-Bestiary"
                        },
                        "page": 47
                    },
                    "subtype": "locations",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Locations",
                    "image": "Sidebar_3_Locations.png"
                },
                {
                    "name": "Bugbear Treasure",
                    "type": "sidebar",
                    "sections": [],
                    "text": "Though bugbears don\u2019t have much\nconcern for treasure, they\u2019re prone\nto keeping gruesome trophies.\nSome might keep a leather cord\nstrung with ears from their victims,\nwhile others collect severed fingers\nor noses. Bits of valuable jewelry\ncan sometimes remain on these\ngrisly prizes.",
                    "source": {
                        "name": "Bestiary",
                        "link": {
                            "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01y0m?Pathfinder-Bestiary"
                        },
                        "page": 47
                    },
                    "subtype": "treasure_and_rewards",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Treasure and Rewards",
                    "image": "Sidebar_5_TreasureAndRewards.png"
                }
            ],
            "text": "These stealthy and cruel goblinoid creatures delight in spreading fear and tormenting their victims. Bugbears are the monsters lurking in the closet and hiding under the bed. Preying on remote farmsteads, bugbears reveal their presence with thumps in the night or creaks of boards to build lurking dread and arouse suspicion and fear.",
            "source": {
                "name": "Bestiary",
                "link": {
                    "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01y0m?Pathfinder-Bestiary"
                },
                "page": 47
            }
        }
    ],
